snippet.title: G2 vs. T1 - VALORANT Masters Bangkok - Grand Final
snippet.description:
From February 20th to March 2nd, Masters Bangkok will bring together the worldâ€™s best VALORANT players for an epic showdown. This first global event of the 2025 VALORANT Champions Tour will feature eight teams representing the four International Leagues. Teams qualified for Masters by placing in the top two at their respective Kick-Off tournaments. The stakes are high, as the top four teams will earn valuable Championship Points and move one step closer to competing in Champions Paris.
Masters Bangkok will be split into two parts - the Swiss Stage and the Bracket Stage. In the Swiss Stage, teams will need to secure 2 victories before they accumulate 2 losses across a maximum of three rounds to advance out of Swiss. Each match will be a Best of Three series. A random draw will pair the competitors, a double elimination bracket will narrow them down, and weâ€™ll close out with a Best-of-Five series in the Lower and Grand Finals. The last team standing will earn the title of Masters Bangkok Champion.
Weâ€™re proud to work with our fantastic partners throughout 2025: AWS, HyperX, Mastercard, OMEN, Red Bull, Secretlab, and Verizon.
Make sure to follow the official VALORANT Esports social channels for additional information:
